OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F377A1756487219
OL,3,CReform councillors' media blackout
OL,4,Ccondemned as blow to democracy
OL,6,F"We've just provided challenging,
OL,7,Ffair, scrutinising coverage to the
OL,8,Fparty now in charge of the largest
OL,9,Flocal authority in our area.
OL,11,F"A free press scrutinising parties in
OL,12,Fcharge of councils like this is
OL,13,Fimportant, whatever your political
OL,14,Fbeliefs."
OL,16,FThe National Union of Journalists and
OL,17,FSociety of Editors match Oliver's
OL,18,Fconcerns that the council, which has a
OL,19,Fbudget of over a billion pounds and a
OL,20,Fpopulation of 800,000 people, will no
OL,21,Flonger be subject to proper scrutiny.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/9
