OL,3,CReform councillors' media blackout
OL,4,Ccondemned as blow to democracy
OL,6,FDawn Alford, from the Society of
OL,7,FEditors, stated, "Political parties
OL,8,Fshould really welcome scrutiny and not
OL,9,Fsilence it. A free press is not a
OL,10,Fprivilege to be granted when it suits
OL,11,Fthose in power - it's a pillar of our
OL,12,Fdemocracy.
OL,14,F"Shutting out journalists is shutting
OL,15,Fout the public."
OL,17,FLocals in Mansfield were equally
OL,18,Funimpressed, with one saying: "They
OL,19,Fshould talk to the local paper".
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/9
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
